  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are&nbsp;labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. Each figure shows a rectangular object made of four spheres connected by four rods. Figure 1 shows the rectangular object oriented with its long sides vertical, and a dashed vertical axis is drawn through the object’s center of mass. Figure 2 shows the rectangular object oriented with its long sides horizontal, and a dashed vertical axis is drawn through the object’s center of mass.\" src=\"/images/f08183732d249c1b92c9e6034ee9cba3.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A rectangular rigid body consists of four spheres of equal mass connected by rods with negligible mass. The length of the long side of the rectangle is twice that of the short side. In Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, the system is oriented as shown and rotates about the dashed axis that passes through the center of mass of the system. The rotational inertia about the axis is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l sub 1\"><math alttext=\"l sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. In Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, the system is turned <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"90 degrees\"><math alttext=\"90 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">°</mi></math></span></span> and rotates about the dashed axis shown that also passes through the center of mass of the system. The rotational inertia of the system about the axis is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l sub 2\"><math alttext=\"l sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly compares <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l sub 2\"><math alttext=\"l sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"l sub 1\"><math alttext=\"l sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>I</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
